{"lemma":"بَهِيمَةٌ","slug":"بَهِيمَةٌ","root":"ب.ه.م","root_slug":"ب-ه-م","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-ه-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"بَهِيمَة","root":"بهم","pos":"N","occurrence_count":3},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n3455"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D9%8E%D9%87%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%85%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"beast, head of cattle"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"According to Arthur Jeffery it appears first in discussions of dietary laws and thus is likely borrowed from Hebrew בְּהֵמָה (bəhēmā́). Else it belongs to the root ب ه م (b h m) to which there is also بَهْمَة (bahma, “lamb”). Compare Ugaritic 𐎁𐎅𐎎𐎚 (bhmt) and Ge'ez ብህመ (bəhmä, “to be dumb, to be speechless”)."},"ipa":["/ba.hiː.ma/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n3455","headword_ar":"بَهِيمَةٌ","root":"bhm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A beast; a brute;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any quadruped,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Akh, M, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"even if in the water,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Akh, M, K,) [i. e.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the land"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the sea;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;) and (so in the Msb, but in the K “or”)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any animal that does not discriminate:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj, Msb, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bahaAy^imu","text_ar":"بَهَايِمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, Msb, K.)"}],"source_refs":["Akh","M","Msb","K","Zj"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}